[01-Mar-22 02:37 AM] Sigyn#0001
by learning the tech first. Im giving you the best thing I personnaly use to invest into a project. Im asking question to myself while im seraching :

- is it decentralized ?
- is it innovative / new ? If so, how far they are into the development, if not, are they doing better than others doing this ?
- Am I gonna use this token / the protocol ? 
- Is it on a chain that already proved itself (when I want to play it safe)
- I check scalability / interoperability
- Is it audited ? 


All these terms are "must know" if you want to search good. I got into LUNA around 1$
I got into ATOM under 
I got into AKASH at 0.8 I think
and so on for this last 12 months only. 

This method works. I dont touch tokens / protocols that can be hyped I dont invest to "trade" I invest where the tech interest me and I never invest where shit is not decentralized, dont build anything or taking forever, are not doing something inovative etc...

[12-Apr-22 05:59 PM] Sigyn#0001
oh I get a good one on this. A thing I heard a while ago. 
not having confidence means FEAR.

FEAR is a filter you have in your brain that is unrealistic most of time.
How can we demonstrate this ? 

take 2 boys at the beach. One jumps into the waves. The other is scared.
What makes them act different ? a filter one has which is fear. 

How to avoid ? ask this question : 
Whats the worst that can happen ? 
Is it realistically about to happen ? 
Generally speaking its always NO 

Then why the fear ? the filter. You control this filter, dont let it control you. 

So everytime you fear to do something, think about this filter that is unrealistic and made up of worst case scenario that will probably never happen. 

Fight 1 fire a day, do something you are scared to do everyday even a little one
And congrat yourself afterward and do more day after day ğŸ˜‰
